{
  "stem": "12612.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I remember looking at the baby down at the ground, and the baby was dismembered.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Then we had to go stand on appel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Now, it didn't matter if it was freezing winter or if it was boiling hot in the summer, we had to stand dead still like this to be counted.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I don't know if there were hundreds of us or thousands of us, we had to stand there and be counted.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "If anybody sneezed, they started all over again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Somebody coughed, started all over again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I remember tugging on my mother skirt and telling her I had to go to the bathroom.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And she said, shh.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I don't know what I did, but we had to stand there and be counted all over again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Now, in my mind, I remember standing naked with everybody.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But I think my mother said that we were not naked, just that we were cold, and we were wearing almost nothing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were able to-- to run to the-- to camps-- when they got us, we were able to take a little bundle of stuff.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we outgrew that, my parents would barter stuff.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When the French people came to the camps, they were not used to the hunger yet.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were well-fed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they had nice clothes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just-- French style.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They knew what to buy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had good stuff on them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father and my mother each would save three days' ration of bread and give it to them for a little sweater for my-- outfit for my brother.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or a sweater for my mother, my father saved his bread.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so that way they got clothing back and forth.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was my mother's job to serve-- bring the soup-- quote, 'soup'.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
